From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Scrub WebRTC ICE candidates at the network stack

Detection vector: WebRTC fingerprinting creates a RTCPeerConnection,
gathers ICE candidates (which contain local IP addresses), and reads
the SDP offer. The local IPs uniquely identify the device and reveal
VPN/proxy usage when the real IP differs from the WebRTC IP.

This patch filters ICE candidates at the network layer, removing
host-type candidates that expose local/private IP addresses.

Surface: webrtc
Closes: WebRTC IP leak, ICE candidate fingerprinting

--- a/third_party/webrtc/pc/peer_connection.cc
+++ b/third_party/webrtc/pc/peer_connection.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void PeerConnection::OnIceCandidate(
+  // AgenticBrowser: filter host-type ICE candidates to prevent
+  // local IP leakage. Only relay and srflx candidates are passed
+  // through. This is applied at the C++ layer so no JS override
+  // is detectable.
+  if (candidate.type() == "host" && !candidate.address().IsAnyIP()) {
+    // Skip host candidate to avoid leaking local IP.
+    return;
+  }
